comments: Thybulle (PHI) legally contests the jump shot attempt by Tatum (BOS), who extends his leg and creates the marginal contact.
Curry (PHI) steps out of bounds during his drive to the basket.
Embiid (PHI) moves along Schroder's (BOS) path to the basket and makes marginal contact that does not affect his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Maxey's (PHI) path and does not deliver contact.
Curry (PHI) makes contact to Schroder's (BOS) arm and it causes him to lose control of the ball.
Maxey (PHI) extends his off-arm towards Schroder (BOS), whose momentum carries him in the same direction and the contact is marginal.
Embiid (PHI) does not make an unnatural basketball play when Smart (BOS) inadvertently moves into his elbow.

Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Tatum's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact.  After the initial contact, Embiid continues moving laterally but does not initiate any contact with Tatum.
Maxey (PHI) leans forward into Horford (BOS) as he sets the screen but the contact is marginal as Horford disengages and goes underneath.
Harris (PHI) places an arm in Schroder's (BOS) path but the contact is marginal and does not affect his SQBR.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver contact.  The two players engage and disengage following the initial contact in the post.
Williams III (BOS) cleanly blocks Niang's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
